text: Guys, as bad as it may seem, we are not fucked. Considering our population density, our growing numbers of 300, 400 and 700 is considered decent. For a country as compact as Singapore, we should be seeing thousands at this point but that isnt the case. Look at the top few countries, they have very widespread population but still is transmitting at a faster rate than we are(some while under lockdown). The government have also said that the first 2 weeks will be crucial. The CB will flush out most of the clusters and infected. Dont forget that this virus takes about a week or 2 before developing symptoms in some cases and we are witnessing the evidence as more and more gets tested positive. For all we know, some of these could have been old cases that tested positive near the end of 2 weeks. The best we can do now is listen to the government and cooperate because who understands the situation better than they do? Stay up to date as well through reputable news sources. Its gonna be a long and tiring fight for our frontliners, dont be dead weights.
